:h1.Menu

:h2 res=&PANEL_MENUFILE..File
:p.Menu items for importing and exporting files.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUIMPORTFILE..Import File
:p.Inserts text from a given file into the message window. This is only
available when editing a message.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUEXPORTFILE..Export File
:p.Writes the current message to a text file on disk. This is only available
when reading messages.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUFILEECHOTOSS..Write Echotoss now
:p.Write the echotoss file immediately.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUFILESHELL..Start command shell
:p.Starts a commandline session. The program used as shell is specified
in CONFIG.SYS via OS2_SHELL.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUFILEPRINT..Print
:p.Print current message

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUFILEPRINTSETUP..Printer setup
:p.Setup options for printing

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUEXIT..Exit FleetStreet
:p.Exits the program. Changes to the configuration will be saved.

:h2 res=&PANEL_MENUEDIT..Edit
:p.Menu items to perform changes to a messages and for interaction
with the clipboard.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUEDITCUT..Cut
:p.Copies marked text in the message window to the clipboard and deletes
the marked text.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUEDITCOPY..Copy
:p.Copies marked text in the message window to the clipboard. If no text is
marked, the whole message is copied to the clipboard.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUEDITPASTE..Paste
:p.Inserts the contents of the clipboard into the message window.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUEDITCLEAR..Clear
:p.Deletes marked text in the message window.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUEDITUNDO..Undo
:p.Takes back the latest changes in the message window.
:p.:hp8.Note&colon.:ehp8. This does only apply to text in the message window,
not to whole messages. Deleted messages can not be recovered.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUEDITDELLINE..Delete Line
:p.Deletes the current line in the message window.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUEDITSEARCH..Search
:p.Searches for text in the current message.

