:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGMOVE..Move Message
:p.Move the current message to a different area

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGCOPY..Copy Message
:p.Copy the current message to a different area

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGFORWARD..Forward Message
:p.Forward the current message

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGNEW..New message
:p.Write new message in the current area.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGCHANGE..Change
:p.Change current message.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGREPLY..Reply
:p.Reply to current message.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGDELETE..Delete
:p.Delete current message.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGFIND..Find
:p.Find text in a message in this area or in all areas.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGBCAST..Broadcast
:p.Broadcast-delete or broadcast-modify the current message.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGBCDELETE..Broadcast delete
:p.Broadcast-delete the current message.
:p.There are several restrictions for using this function&colon.
:ul compact.
:li.It can only be used in echomail areas
:li.The message must be local
:li.The message must be already scanned out
:li.The message must have a MSGID kludge line
:eul.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGBCMODIFY..Broadcast modify
:p.Broadcast-modify the current message.
:p.There are several restrictions for using this function&colon.
:ul compact.
:li.It can only be used in echomail areas
:li.The message must be local
:li.The message must be already scanned out
:li.The message must have a MSGID kludge line
:eul.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGMARKMSG..Mark message
:p.Set a mark on the current message

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGUNMARKMSG..Unmark message
:p.Remove mark on current message

:h2 res=&PANEL_MENUSPECIAL..Special
:p.Special FleetStreet functions

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGXPOST..Crosspost Message
:p.Post the message in more than one area
:p.If this menu item is checked, you've already selected the destination areas.
Select this menu item again to uncheck it.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGREQUEST..Request Files
:p.Request files from the current message

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGCCOPY..Carbon Copy
:p.Send the message to more than one receipient using a carbon copy list.
:p.If this menu item is checked, you've already selected a carbon copy list.
Select this menu item again to uncheck it.

:h3 res=&PANEL_MENUMSGQUICKCC..Quick carbon copy
:p.Send the message to more than one receipient using a carbon copy list.
:p.Quick carbon copy is different from normal carbon copy is several aspects&colon.
:ul compact.
:li.You don't have to create a new list and name it.
:li.The list is not saved.
:eul.

:h3 id=markmsg res=&PANEL_MENUMSGMARK..Catchup
:p.If you haven't used FleetStreet for reading in a particular message base before,
all messages are marked as "unread". Therefore the message thread list will show
you all messages in that area. Because you may have read these messages before,
this menu item provides a way to mark all the messages as "read".
After you've done that, the thread list will show only messages that are
"really" unread, i.e. messages that were added to this area after you've used
this function.
:p.This function is usually only needed after you've switched to FleetStreet
and want to bring "old" message areas up to date. FleetStreet will maintain the
"read" flag automatically in the future.

